13, 15, 17 East 35th Street, north side, adjoining the N.W. corner of Madison Avenue. These buildings will be demolished after 1925, when the International Combustion Building is erected on the site.
1916.

Neg. # - 1405

17-1 East and 1 West 35th Street, north side, from west of Madison Avenue to and including Fifth. 1916.

Neg # - 1406

Madison Avenue, north from 35th Street, showing transition era in the J.P. Morgan neighborhood. Preparations are already made to remove the buildings on left. They will be replaced by Marshall Field building, No. 200 Madison Avenue.

The church shown in part at the extreme right is the Protestant Episcopal Church of the Incarnation. On the N.E. corner of 36th Street may be seen the Madison Avenue side of the J.P. Morgan residence, which will shortly be remodeled as an annex to the Morgan Library. On the N.E. corner of 37th Street, in front of the large apartment hotel, is the old Delmar residence, the home since 1923 of the National Democratic Club.

April 1925.

Brown Brothers, Photographers.

29-39 East 35th street, north side, between Madison and Park
Avenues. Nos. 29, 31, and 35 are old stables, now garages.
February 23, 1931.

P. L. Sperr.

29-17 East 35th Street, north side, at Madison Avenue, including
the Church of the Incarnation (Protestant Episcopal) and the
new International Combustion Building.
February 23, 1931.

P. L. Sperr.

East 35th Street, south side, east from Madison to Park Aves., and
showing on the right side a structure that will be demolished in conjunction
with several other Madison Ave. buildings. Upon this corner site will rise
a 15-story apartment house that will be known as 20 East 35th Street. On
the extreme left is a vacant lot at the rear of an apartment house at the
S.W. corner of Park Ave.

July, 22, 1937.

P. L. Sperr.

East 35th St., south side, west from (No.24) a point slightly
east of Madison Ave., and across same, to 5th Avenue (right) and
showing across a vacant lot at the S. E. corner of Madison Ave.,
the B. Altman & Co. Department Store occupying the entire block
bounded by Madison & 5th Avenues and E. 34th to 35th Sts. At the
afore mentioned corner clearance, a modern 14 story apartment
building (No. 20 E. 35th St.) will shortly rise.

Feb. 4, 1938.

P. L. Sperr.

Neg # 4551
